There are other means by which a company may obtain an H-1-B exemption, one of which is by showing the ability to hire only US citizens and qualified permanent residents for at least 75 percent of its available positions within the one-year period immediately prior to the petition filing date.

There are two primary methods to obtain H-1 exemption. One method is the "job market survey" process. The other method is the ability to prove that the employer can only find US citizen or H-1 resident applicants for its positions.

It is common for the employer to use both methods to show eligibility for exemption and get this done through 3rd party verification.
